<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="191" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,717]" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,325,582,608]" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Discussion</emphasis>
. This species remains poorly known. Our redescription is based on notes taken by the second author during his last stay in Rio de Janeiro and on available photo of the 
<typeStatus box="[915,967,619,645]" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">type</typeStatus>
. The presence in 
<collectingCountry box="[1163,1274,619,645]" name="Argentina" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Argentina</collectingCountry>
remains to be established, as the only female specimen cited by Carpintero 
<emphasis box="[839,889,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">et al</emphasis>
. from this country has been putatively identified in the present work as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1860" box="[404,644,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Valdasus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="191" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schoenherri">
<emphasis box="[404,644,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="191">Valdasus schoenherri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
